<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="196" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d196">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.857/404</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at London</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SRP1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-14">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 14, 1917</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 2.45 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>American Consul, Plymouth, reports British <hi rend="italic">East
                                Point</hi>, London for Philadelphia, torpedoed 9th, 5. p.m., about
                            15 miles west of Eddystone Lighthouse. <hi rend="italic">East Point</hi>
                            not warned, carried one gun aft, armed patrol boat near by. Crew of 45
                            left <hi rend="italic">East Point</hi> in four; boats, all saved.
                                <persName>John Webber</persName> of, 159 Fougeron Street, Buffalo,
                            fireman, and <persName>Edward Ellis</persName>, 565 Cortland Avenue,
                            Brooklyn, seaman, both American citizens, have made affidavits at
                            Plymouth.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_SRP1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Skinner</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>